ntil you do something to reverse it?  I know I havn't done anything to reverse it because I havn't played since that time.  Unless hunting in Netherbian Lair has an averse reaction which I don't see why it would.<br><br>Any ideas?<br><br>Jaroo Dooger of Tinker's Pride<br>Wizard of the 24th spire <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 244<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/8/02 8:28:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1307.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does this really happen with factions?</span><hr size=1> It maybe an intential change or an accident that was made by Verant. <br><br>On a side note. I am NOT saying this is why your faction may have changed. I am simply pointing out something I have observed connected to this line of thought.<br><br>I have noticed that in Luclin INVISIBLE faction changes do occur. Most noticable was the loss of faction with the Troglodyte like guys in Fungus Grove. In the early days after release no faction loss was recorded in the chat window when you killed them, but eventually you became KOS from killing them. Other places I have &quot;seemed&quot; to notice this also. Several zones with mobs that dont con KOS at first and NO faction loss is recorded in the chat window, I have noticed after killing some that my faction is less than it was (usually from Indifferent to Apprehensive).<br><br>This could be perception on my part, maybe I missed a message in another zone, with another mob, that effected it. I have noticed that also occurs, mobs share faction in places. Or similiar mobs that are social, that are not naturally KOS will attack if your engaged with kos mobs. The original mob has no faction but its &quot;ally&quot; does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujaroodooger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaroo Dooger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/9/02 4:14:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1307.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does this really happen with factions?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the help, Twotribes.  I appreciate it.  It is definatly something to look into and that I'm sure we should all be aware of.<br><br>Jaroo Dooger of Tinker's Pride<br>Wizard of the 24th Spire <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unakath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nakath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/9/02 5:19:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1307.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Does this really happen with factions?</span><hr size=1> the necklace you get from trade commissioner gives 2 or 3 shifts... you MIGHT have to periodically put it on to get faction. <p>Nakath<BR>The Esoteric Order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 397<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/9/02 7:15:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1307.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Faction messages ..</span><hr size=1> .. used to never come out.  I think they were added perhaps 3 months after release.  It could be that some new mobs behave like release mobs -- change your faction without warning.  Verant does like that method much better than the messages.  They resisted putting messages in.<br><br>They also used to have &quot;instant-kos&quot; mobs.  One kill and they'd completely destroy your faction.  Some of the guards were like this.  People would kill one just to see if they could and then find out (much later) they were KOS all over. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxelenathebard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XelenaTheBard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/9/02 11:08:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1307.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction messages ..</span><hr size=1> With all the wacky stuff they've done for luclin, invisable messages wouldn't surprise me.<br><br>Parse my logs, though, and I see an &quot;invisable&quot; hit to ORC faction that adds up to Deathfist + Crushbone + Orc Highway, though......<br><br>Things like that happen. Parse a log and find out what you might have going for you.<br><br><br> <p><img src="http://home.san.rr.com/rikku/Xe